    public enum Instruction
extends java.lang.Enum<Instruction>
    An instruction for Rob on how to move on a Grid. The method execute(Coordinate) has been implemented as a convenience method to execute the instruction.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NORTH

        public static final Instruction NORTH
        Instruction to move towards the north. If rob is moved from coordinate c1 towards the north, the y part of new coordinate c2 will be one smaller than that of c1.

      • EAST

        public static final Instruction EAST
        Instruction to move towards the east. If rob is moved from coordinate c1 towards the east, the x part of new coordinate c2 will be one bigger than that of c1.

      • SOUTH

        public static final Instruction SOUTH
        Instruction to move towards the south. If rob is moved from coordinate c1 towards the south, the y part of new coordinate c2 will be one bigger than that of c1.

      • WEST

        public static final Instruction WEST
        Instruction to move towards the west. If rob is moved from coordinate c1 towards the west, the x part of new coordinate c2 will be one smaller than that of c1.

      • PAUSE

        public static final Instruction PAUSE
        Instruction to wait. Rob does not change his position.

      • execute

        public Coordinate execute​(Coordinate cell)
        Executes the instruction to make a move. Every move takes one second. Also the PAUSE instruction takes one second.
        Parameters:
        cell - the current cell
        Returns:
        the coordinates of the cell after the instruction has been executed.
